<tool id="pair_strains" name="Pair strains" version="@TOOL_VERSION@+galaxy@VERSION_SUFFIX@" profile="@PROFILE@">
    <description>Enumerate unordered FASTA pairs as a list:paired collection</description>
    <macros>
        <import>macros.xml</import>
    </macros>
    <expand macro="requirements"/>
    <required_files>
        <include path="pair_strains.py"/>
    </required_files>
    <version_command>python '$__tool_directory__/pair_strains.py' --help | head -1</version_command>
    <command detect_errors="aggressive"><![CDATA[
mkdir -p pairs &&
## Build a TSV manifest of <element_identifier>\t<path> by iterating the
## input list collection via Cheetah.
#for $el in $input
printf '%s\t%s\n' '$el.element_identifier' '$el' >> manifest.tsv &&
#end for
python '$__tool_directory__/pair_strains.py'
    --manifest manifest.tsv
    --outdir pairs
    --ext fa
    $include_self
    $both_directions
    ]]></command>
    <inputs>
        <param name="input" type="data_collection" collection_type="list" format="fasta,fasta.gz"
               label="Masked FASTA list collection"
               help="A 'list' collection with one FASTA per strain; the element identifier is used as the strain name."/>
        <param name="include_self" type="boolean" truevalue="--include-self" falsevalue=""
               checked="false" label="Include self-pairs (A vs A)"
               help="Also emit each strain paired with itself."/>
        <param name="both_directions" type="boolean" truevalue="--both-directions" falsevalue=""
               checked="false" label="Both directions (A vs B and B vs A)"
               help="Emit ordered pairs in both directions instead of only the unordered pair A&lt;B."/>
    </inputs>
    <outputs>
        <collection name="pairs" type="list:paired" label="${tool.name} on ${on_string}: strain pairs">
            <discover_datasets pattern="(?P&lt;identifier_0&gt;.+)_(?P&lt;identifier_1&gt;forward|reverse)\.fa"
                               format="fasta" directory="pairs" recurse="false"/>
        </collection>
    </outputs>
    <tests>
        <test expect_num_outputs="1">
            <param name="input">
                <collection type="list">
                    <element name="A" value="a.fasta" ftype="fasta"/>
                    <element name="B" value="b.fasta" ftype="fasta"/>
                    <element name="C" value="c.fasta" ftype="fasta"/>
                </collection>
            </param>
            <param name="include_self" value="false"/>
            <param name="both_directions" value="false"/>
            <output_collection name="pairs" type="list:paired" count="3">
                <element name="A__vs__B">
                    <element name="forward">
                        <assert_contents>
                            <has_text text=">A_chr1"/>
                        </assert_contents>
                    </element>
                    <element name="reverse">
                        <assert_contents>
                            <has_text text=">B_chr1"/>
                        </assert_contents>
                    </element>
                </element>
                <element name="A__vs__C">
                    <element name="forward">
                        <assert_contents>
                            <has_text text=">A_chr1"/>
                        </assert_contents>
                    </element>
                    <element name="reverse">
                        <assert_contents>
                            <has_text text=">C_chr1"/>
                        </assert_contents>
                    </element>
                </element>
                <element name="B__vs__C">
                    <element name="forward">
                        <assert_contents>
                            <has_text text=">B_chr1"/>
                        </assert_contents>
                    </element>
                    <element name="reverse">
                        <assert_contents>
                            <has_text text=">C_chr1"/>
                        </assert_contents>
                    </element>
                </element>
            </output_collection>
        </test>
        <test expect_num_outputs="1">
            <param name="input">
                <collection type="list">
                    <element name="A" value="a.fasta" ftype="fasta"/>
                    <element name="B" value="b.fasta" ftype="fasta"/>
                </collection>
            </param>
            <param name="include_self" value="true"/>
            <param name="both_directions" value="false"/>
            <output_collection name="pairs" type="list:paired" count="3">
                <element name="A__vs__A">
                    <element name="forward">
                        <assert_contents>
                            <has_text text=">A_chr1"/>
                        </assert_contents>
                    </element>
                    <element name="reverse">
                        <assert_contents>
                            <has_text text=">A_chr1"/>
                        </assert_contents>
                    </element>
                </element>
                <element name="A__vs__B">
                    <element name="forward">
                        <assert_contents>
                            <has_text text=">A_chr1"/>
                        </assert_contents>
                    </element>
                    <element name="reverse">
                        <assert_contents>
                            <has_text text=">B_chr1"/>
                        </assert_contents>
                    </element>
                </element>
                <element name="B__vs__B">
                    <element name="forward">
                        <assert_contents>
                            <has_text text=">B_chr1"/>
                        </assert_contents>
                    </element>
                    <element name="reverse">
                        <assert_contents>
                            <has_text text=">B_chr1"/>
                        </assert_contents>
                    </element>
                </element>
            </output_collection>
        </test>
        <test expect_num_outputs="1">
            <param name="input">
                <collection type="list">
                    <element name="A" value="a.fasta" ftype="fasta"/>
                    <element name="B" value="b.fasta" ftype="fasta"/>
                </collection>
            </param>
            <param name="include_self" value="false"/>
            <param name="both_directions" value="true"/>
            <output_collection name="pairs" type="list:paired" count="2">
                <element name="A__vs__B">
                    <element name="forward">
                        <assert_contents>
                            <has_text text=">A_chr1"/>
                        </assert_contents>
                    </element>
                    <element name="reverse">
                        <assert_contents>
                            <has_text text=">B_chr1"/>
                        </assert_contents>
                    </element>
                </element>
                <element name="B__vs__A">
                    <element name="forward">
                        <assert_contents>
                            <has_text text=">B_chr1"/>
                        </assert_contents>
                    </element>
                    <element name="reverse">
                        <assert_contents>
                            <has_text text=">A_chr1"/>
                        </assert_contents>
                    </element>
                </element>
            </output_collection>
        </test>
    </tests>
    <help format="markdown"><![CDATA[
**Pair strains** — build a `list:paired` collection of unordered strain pairs.

Given a masked-FASTA **list** collection (one FASTA per strain, with the
strain name carried as the element identifier), this tool enumerates all
distinct pairs and emits a **`list:paired`** collection. Each paired
element is identified as `{A}__vs__{B}`, with the `forward` slot holding
strain A's FASTA and the `reverse` slot holding strain B's FASTA.

This feeds all-vs-all pairwise pangenome steps (e.g. per-pair `wfmash`
mapping) where each job needs exactly two assemblies.

-----

**Inputs**

- *Masked FASTA list collection* — a `list` collection; element
  identifiers are the strain names.
- *Include self-pairs* — also emit `A__vs__A` (default off).
- *Both directions* — emit `A__vs__B` **and** `B__vs__A` (default off:
  only the unordered pair `A<B`).

**Output**

- A `list:paired` collection. With N strains and the defaults, this is
  `N*(N-1)/2` pairs (e.g. 3 strains → 3 pairs).

-----

**Implementation note**

The wrapper iterates the input collection to write a
`<identifier>\t<path>` manifest, then a small bundled Python helper
(`pair_strains.py`, stdlib only) symlinks each pair's two FASTAs as
`{A}__vs__{B}_forward.fa` / `{A}__vs__{B}_reverse.fa` into a working
directory. Galaxy's `discover_datasets` regex
`(?P<identifier_0>.+)_(?P<identifier_1>forward|reverse)\.fa` then groups
them into the `list:paired` structure.

Source: authored for the Pv4 pangenome pipeline
(`v3/pipeline/impl/scripts`).
    ]]></help>
    <expand macro="citations"/>
</tool>
